channel.description:
Hello!
I was happy to see this morning that SirSickSik and TB had sorted out SSS's issues with Github, so I happily did a sync library.
But when I hit sync library I got this message: Status: community (1.0.12,anon)
Nothing happened. I thought it was because Axo for some reason had "forgotten" about my prefix so I entered it again. I havent used it for a while. Now I get a messages that I have never seen before:
Axoloti version : 1.0.12-1-0-g4de2b632 build time : 08/02/2017 00:15:42 GMT Link to firmware CRC E95BAC96 Status: factory (1.0.12,anon) : OK ( 1.0.12,clean ) Status : home : OK Status: community (1.0.12,jaffasplaffa) : OK ( 1.0.12,dirty ) Changes for: community (1.0.12,jaffasplaffa) untracked: objects/jaffa/dyn/mbext1.axo untracked: patches/sptnk/._rectangular window test patch.axp8292440972423511469.tmp untracked: objects/jaffa/dyn/ng1.axo untracked: objects/jaffa/dyn/compb3.axo untracked: objects/jaffa/dyn/compb2.axo untracked folders: objects/jaffa/dyn Status : Objects : OK Status : Objects2 : OK Status : subs : OK No available USB device found with matching PID/VID search path : /Users/jakobskouborg/Documents/axoloti/axoloti-factory/objects search path : /Users/jakobskouborg/Documents/axoloti/objects search path : /Users/jakobskouborg/Documents/axoloti/axoloti-contrib/objects search path : /Volumes/Jaffa II/1. Music stuff/Axoloti/Axoloti Stuff/Objects/objects
I have not touched or uploaded anything for Axoloti in months and last time I used it it worked 100% fine and now I get all these weird message I have newer seen before
@thetechnobear any ideas?

cool, sorry couldn't determine underlying issue....

what I might do for the next release is get Axoloti to report the commit id to the console, this would enable us to see where Axoloti currently thinks the last change is.... i.e. where has it synchronised too.

( I dont want to go and find the 'latest change' on github, as that implies network activity, to go find it, and I want axoloti to not touch the network unless explicitly requested to do so (using Sync, or if you enable autosync.)

anyway, glad you up n running again.

these will get uploaded (except the sptnk one) to git when you next hit sync.

I just tried and they didnt get updated.

About the anon issue. It might be related to that long long time ago I had another profile, which was deleted from this forum. And when I entered the forum again, you Marc didnt something so i could keep the jaffa prefix. It has worked fine up to now iirc.

thetechnobear:

i see SSS osc/DX7 so if you don't then i suggest you do a reset library... but as far as i can see your library is sync'd correctly (note: its case sensitive)

I have just resynced many times and I dobbelt checke that I used the right log in for the com.lib, the same as used for Github and still dont see any new objects from sirsicksik. Yes i know it is case sensitive and have taken that into consideration. There are nothing new from him in the comlib as far as I can see.

Argh something is going on here.....

item.title: Syncing library problem!
item.dc:creator: @thetechnobear Mark Harris
item.description:
@thetechnobear wrote:

jaffasplaffa:

So no clue what this "untracked" means.

untracked means they are not tracked by GIT, i.e. they are not considered to be in the library.

jaffasplaffa:

That is not my current prefix, that is the one I had for my old profile. I just updated the prefix information a few minutes ago and after restart axo it seems like it changed it again.

well thats where you put these files... so at some point you had your prefix as this.

anyway just delete them if you have no idea what they are

dirty = changes are present, that will be committed when you next to sync (but only under your prefix)
clean = you have no local changes

anon = anonymous i.e. you are not using an account/prefix , correct for factory... and also for non-contributors for community library.

as i said none of these are errors, they are information...

i see SSS osc/DX7 so if you don't then i suggest you do a reset library... but as far as i can see your library is sync'd correctly (note: its case sensitive)

item.title: Syncing library problem!
item.dc:creator: @thetechnobear Mark Harris
item.description:
@thetechnobear wrote:

ok this is not an error as such...

this is merely saying that you have new objects (untracked means added to GIT library)

these will get uploaded (except the sptnk one) to git when you next hit sync.
so you need to decide if that is what you want to do or not.
... if you can simply delete/move them

ideally what I would do if your not sure is, given the time since you last did anything is:
move them away , say on your desktop , do a sync , check everything is as expected, and then put them back, and do a sync to upload them.
... its not strictly necessary, but if you have been updating on another machine, this will ensure you don't end up creating some kind of conflict due to updates from two places.
